Description: Add inode/directory MIME type to desktop file   Fix typo in desktop file   Experimental code that allows to open folders. Needs feedback   Use continue instead of return not to stop loop   Use File[] instead of Array   Implement changes in review, improve readibility   Make loop code easier to understand and more performant   Implement changes in review   Use try/catch to handle errors in list_directory   Get files from subdirectories too   Lint   Make field private   Simplify code calling is_directory   Move is_directory declaration to inline   Move rest of the try/catch outside   Declare dir outside in try/catch   Co-authored-by: Leo lenemter@gmail.com   Give flatpak access to users Music folder   Ignore flatpack files   Comment and debugging message   Remove unneeded linebreak   Use type inference in File declaration at list_directory    Co-authored-by: Leo lenemter@gmail.com Co-authored-by: Jeremy Wootten jeremy@elementaryos.org
Description Abstract: Add inode/directory MIME type to desktop file Fix typo in desktop file Experimental code that allows to open folders. Needs feedback Use continue instead of return not to stop loop Use File[] instead of Array Implement changes in review, improve readibility Make loop code easier to understand and more performant Implement changes in review Use try/catch to handle errors in list_directory Get files from subdirectories too Lint Make field private Simplify code calling is_directory Move is_directory declaration to inline Move rest of the try/catch outside Declare dir outside in try/catch Co-authored-by: Leo lenemter@gmail.com Give flatpak access to users Music folder Ignore flatpack files Comment and debugging message Remove unneeded linebreak Use type inference in File declaration at list_directory Co-authored-by: Leo lenemter@gmail.com Co-authored-by: Jeremy Wootten jeremy@elementaryos.org
